arxiv.arxiv.Result.doc: An entry in an arXiv query results feed. See the arXiv API User's Manual: Details of Atom Results Returned.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.__init__.doc: Constructs an arXiv search result item. In most cases, prefer using _from_feed_entry to parsing and constructing feed items yourself.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.doi.doc: A URL for the resolved DOI to an external resource if present.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.primary_category.doc: The result's primary arXiv category. See arXiv: Category Taxonomy.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.categories.doc: All of the result's categories. See arXiv: Category Taxonomy.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.links.doc: Up to three URLs associated with this result.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.pdf_url.doc: The URL of a PDF version of this result if present among links.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.get_short_id.doc: Returns the short ID for this result. If the result URL is "http://arxiv.org/abs/quant-ph/0201082v1", result.get_short_id() returns "0201082v1".

arxiv.arxiv.Result.download_pdf.doc: Downloads the PDF for this result to the specified directory. The filename is generated by calling to_filename(self).

arxiv.arxiv.Result.download_source.doc: Downloads the source tarfile for this result to the specified directory. The filename is generated by calling to_filename(self).

arxiv.arxiv.Result.Author.doc: A light inner class for representing a result's authors.

arxiv.arxiv.Result.Link.doc: A light inner class for representing a result's links.

arxiv.arxiv.SortCriterion.doc: A SortCriterion identifies a property by which search results can be sorted. See the arXiv API User's Manual: sort order for return results.

arxiv.arxiv.SortOrder.doc: A SortOrder indicates order in which search results are sorted according to the specified arxiv.SortCriterion. See the arXiv API User's Manual: sort order for return results.

arxiv.arxiv.Search.doc: A specification for a search of arXiv's database. To run a search, use Search.run to use a default client or Client.run with a specific client.

arxiv.arxiv.Search.query.doc: A string query. See the arXiv API User's Manual: Details of Query Construction.

arxiv.arxiv.Search.id_list.doc: A list of arXiv article IDs to which to limit the search. See the arXiv API User's Manual for documentation of the interaction between query and id_list.

arxiv.arxiv.Search.max_results.doc: The maximum number of results to be returned in an execution of this search. To fetch every result available, set max_results=float('inf').

arxiv.arxiv.Search.get.doc: Executes the specified search using a default arXiv API client. For info on those defauts see Client; see also (Client).get.

arxiv.arxiv.Client.doc: Specifies a strategy for fetching results from arXiv's API; it obscures pagination and retry logic, and exposes (Client).get.

arxiv.arxiv.Client.page_size.doc: Maximum number of results fetched in a single API request.

arxiv.arxiv.Client.delay_seconds.doc: Number of seconds to wait between API requests.

arxiv.arxiv.Client.num_retries.doc: Number of times to retry a failing API request.

arxiv.arxiv.Client.get.doc:
Uses this client configuration to fetch one page of the search at a time, yielding the search results one by one, until max_results results have been yielded or there are no more search results.

If all tries fail, raises an UnexpectedEmptyPageError or HTTPError.

For more on using generators, see Generators.

arxiv.arxiv.ArxivError.doc: Common base class for all non-exit exceptions.

arxiv.arxiv.ArxivError.url.doc: The feed URL that could not be fetched.

arxiv.arxiv.UnexpectedEmptyPageError.doc: An error raised when a page of results that should be non-empty is empty. This should never happen in theory, but happens sporadically due to brittleness in the underlying arXiv API; usually resolved by retries.

arxiv.arxiv.UnexpectedEmptyPageError.ret.doc: The request retry number which encountered this error, zero-indexed.

arxiv.arxiv.HTTPError.doc: A non-200 status encountered while fetching a page of results.

arxiv.arxiv.HTTPError.retry.doc: The request retry number which encountered this error, zero-indexed.
